House Resolution 614
By: Representatives Scott of the 76th, Davis of the 87th, and Schofield of the 63rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Lecester "Bill" Allen; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Lecester "Bill" Allen; and
4 WHEREAS, after graduating from Wayne State University, Bill began his career as a teacher
5 in the Detroit Public School System, made his first real estate investment, and later started
6 a daycare business with his wife, Mattie, which expanded to 14 locations; and
7 WHEREAS, by 1984, Bill and Mattie Allen extended their business to K-12th grade private
8 schools at the request of parents and students, graduating their first high school class in 1988
9 and converting four schools into charter schools by 1994; and
10 WHEREAS, in 1999, the Allens expanded their school and real estate holdings across the
11 United States, serving over 12,000 students at 30 locations in more than 20 cities and seven
12 states through both their for-profit and 501(c)(3) non-profit organizations; and
13 WHEREAS, in the pursuit of supporting minority- and women-owned businesses, the Allens
14 created the Allen Entrepreneurial Institute (AEI) at Camp Exposure, a 150-acre complex in
