15 Stonecrest, Georgia, featuring a state-of-the-art conference center, private hotel/dormitory,
16 and a five-story antebellum mansion/conference center named Miss Rebecca's House; and
17 WHEREAS, since its inception in 2001, AEI has educated over 10,000 K-12 students and
18 young adult entrepreneurs from across the globe, including local K-12 school groups, over
19 30 Historical Black Colleges & Universities, and entrepreneurs from more than 20 African
20 countries; and
21 WHEREAS, in 2017, as an extension of the AEI, the Allens established the AEI StartUp
22 Factory, a co-working and event space adjacent to the Mall at Stonecrest; and
23 WHEREAS, Lecester "Bill" Allen possessed the vast wisdom which only comes through
24 experience and the strength of character which is achieved by overcoming the many
25 challenges of life; and
26 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Lecester "Bill" Allen will long be
27 remembered for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
28 had the great fortune of knowing him.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Lecester "Bill" Allen and
31 express their deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
34 family of Lecester "Bill" Allen.
